Florida Territory (1822-03-30)

1822/03/30 -> 1845/03/02

The United States created the Territory of Florida from the provinces of East and West Florida ceded by Spain to the United States. The territory had the same boundaries as the present state of Florida.

(Terr. Papers U.S., 22:389-399; U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 13 [1822], sec. 1/p. 654)
